Running the application:

1. Build a .war file and run it on local Tomcat application server (http://localhost:8080/)
2. Run main method in SimpleNetworkingApplication.java
3. Input your commands on the screen. After the command you will be optionally prompted for additional parameters.



Commands:

write - Write a post on your personal wall
read own - Read all your posts in reverse chronological order
read fol - Read all of your followees posts in reverse chronological order
follow - Follow a specific user by their username
unfollow - Stop following a specific user by their username
logout - Logs you out and lets you login on a different username
help - Lists all of available commands
quit - Stops the application
exit - Stops the application


REST services URLs:

http://localhost:8080/rest/user/ - welcome screen
http://localhost:8080/rest/user/login/{username} - login user from input
http://localhost:8080/rest/user/write - write message
http://localhost:8080/rest/user/read_own - read own messages
http://localhost:8080/rest/user/read_followees - read followees messages
http://localhost:8080/rest/user/follow/{username} - follow selected user
http://localhost:8080/rest/user/unfollow/{username} - unfollow selected user